modules.description: This module implements a TOML encoder for the `Gendarme` library, specifically handling the conversion of OCaml values into TOML-formatted strings. It operates on the `Gendarme.encoder` type, extending it with a `Toml` constructor to support serialization of configuration and data structures used in static analysis rules. Concrete use cases include generating TOML output for linter configurations, analysis results, and rule definitions.

This module implements a TOML encoder for the Gendarme library, providing functions to convert OCaml values to and from TOML format. It works with the `Gendarme.encoder` type and the `Toml.Types.value` type, enabling serialization of static analysis configurations, rule definitions, and analysis results to TOML strings. Key operations include `encode` and `decode` for string-based serialization, and `pack`/`unpack` for value conversion.
